<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/7345516-rik"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1424360341i/7345516._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/7345516-rik">Rik</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It seemed to me that they died in this version of the universe, and their consciousness survived in another one where things played out differently. I<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It seemed to me that they died in this version of the universe, and their consciousness survived in another one where things played out differently. It's playing with the authors idea that consciousness is a quantum effect.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
