      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Adamchuk" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Adamchuk" href="/user/show/53614356-michael-adamchuk">Michael Adamchuk</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/53614356-michael-adamchuk?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/53614356-michael-adamchuk?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/53614356-michael-adamchuk?shelf=rollins-james">rollins-james</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/53614356-michael-adamchuk?shelf=adventure">adventure</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/53614356-michael-adamchuk?shelf=read-2014">read-2014</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3190502823" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12641461903174399253">A military satellite with a top secret experiment crashes in Mongolia. Ina totally unrelated side event, a skull and a book bound with skin is given to a Vatican researcher. The Sigma Force investigates both and discover the effects of dark energy and a historical religious secret. Good story. I like the interweaving of the history with the sci-fi aspects.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


